review: Dr. Dinesh and his team of doctors are all very down to earth. They take care of patients with utmost patience. Their language is very soft and the way in which they treat gives a soothing effect to the patient. I have taken my mom in law who is 80years old. Me and my husband also got the treatment from Doctor Dinesh. I have told.my friends about Dr. Dinesh. I wish Dr. Dinesh should serve the society for longer time and remove the myth about doctors in general and dentists in particular from the minds of the people. Thank you Doctor  for providing and opportunity to give a review.

It is immensely pleasurable to share my feedback about Dr. Dinesh and his team at Outlook Dental Hospital, Trimulghery,  Secunderabad. Heâ€™s the best Iâ€™ve encountered. Patient First Attitude! Dr.Dinesh is an excellent dentist whose main priority is making sure his patients are comfortable and get the best dentistry he can offer. Heâ€™s really very gentle, caring, understanding and showed great concern.

Dr is cool & patient he listens to the problem of patient and suggests a better treatment.
I went for broken teeth he filled it carefully and now it is fine & good.
Even the filled teeth is not looking in x-ray.
I mean that the filling procedure done by doctor is excellent.

Dr Dinesh is so nice, gives proper attentions and expert in his field. Very friendly. The facities at tge clinic are well maintained and up to date

review:
The doctor is friendly but the clinic does not provide the detailed explanation to the patient.
I was recommended a RCT and first session was done by Dr Dinesh and the next session by some junior lady dentist *** *** *** **** ********** **** *** **** ***** *** **** ** *********** ** *************
*** ***** ******** ****** ** **** *** ******* *** *** ******* *** *** ****** ******** ** *** *** **** **** ** * ****** ******* ** ***** ** *** **********

Also there was no explanation of the procedure and that a crown and why a crown will be placed.

Similarly while placing the crown I wasn't given a option to choose the material and by default was given the PFM crown.

For a patient the option to make a informed choice was not given *** ********* *** *** *********

The Doctor allows assistants to examine the patients and the the Assistants are rude enough to tell the patient "vaham ka koi ilaj nahi hota" and then botch up the examination so bad that the pain increases after the examination without really getting an answer to why it was there in the first place.
